{"timestamp": "2025-11-29 17:17:23.286786", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission accepted.\n\nSummary of what I submitted\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"leaf_1\", \"spine_1\", \"controller\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"southbound_port_mismatch\"]\n\nNotes\n- I selected southbound_port_mismatch to represent the most likely class of control-plane/topology mismatch observed: the controller has sessions to all switches but has programmed flows only on leaf_2; leaf_1 shows a drop-all rule and spine_1 has no flows. This aligns with a mismatch in datapath/port mapping or controller logic that causes certain switches/ports to be ignored or misprogrammed.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 3027, "output_tokens": 135, "total_tokens": 3162, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2688}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
